<p><i><b>Project Hail Mary</b></i> is a 2021 <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> novel by American novelist <a href="/wiki/Andy_Weir" title="Andy Weir">Andy Weir</a>.  Set in the near future, the novel centers on <a href="/wiki/Middle_school#United_States" title="Middle school">junior high (middle) school</a>-teacher-turned-<a href="/wiki/Astronaut" title="Astronaut">astronaut</a> Ryland Grace, who wakes up from a <a href="/wiki/Coma" title="Coma">coma</a> afflicted with <a href="/wiki/Amnesia" title="Amnesia">amnesia</a>. He gradually remembers that he was sent to the <a href="/wiki/Tau_Ceti" title="Tau Ceti">Tau Ceti</a> solar system, 12 light-years from Earth, to find a means of reversing a <a href="/wiki/Global_dimming" title="Global dimming">solar dimming</a> event that could cause the extinction of humanity.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> 
</p><p><i>Project Hail Mary</i> has received generally positive reviews, and the book was a finalist for the 2022 <a href="/wiki/Hugo_Award_for_Best_Novel" title="Hugo Award for Best Novel">Hugo Award for Best Novel</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The unabridged <a href="/wiki/Audiobook" title="Audiobook">audiobook</a> is read by <a href="/wiki/Ray_Porter" title="Ray Porter">Ray Porter</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The film rights have been purchased by <a href="/wiki/Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer" title="Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer">Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer</a>. <a href="/wiki/Drew_Goddard" title="Drew Goddard">Drew Goddard</a> (who adapted <i><a href="/wiki/The_Martian_(Weir_novel)" title="The Martian (Weir novel)">The Martian</a></i>, Weir's traditional publishing debut, into <a href="/wiki/The_Martian_(film)" title="The Martian (film)">a 2015 film</a>) is slated to adapt the book into a film. Actor <a href="/wiki/Ryan_Gosling" title="Ryan Gosling">Ryan Gosling</a> plans to star as Grace in the film adaptation.<sup id="cite_ref-variety2020_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-variety2020-4">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
